Field Detail

firstModifiableCharacterInBuffer

private int firstModifiableCharacterInBuffer
A position in the character buffer. The characters before this position shall be considered unmodifiable by the RegexModifier.

This position must not be smaller than the (originally) first modifiable character in the buffer.

This position must not be greater than the size of the buffer plus one.

EXAMPLE: This position is equal to the size of the buffer plus one if the empty string is matched (and processed) and the matching shall be continued after the first character after the empty match. This avoids endless loops.

continueMatching

private boolean continueMatching
True if the matching shall be continued using the characters that already available in the buffer.
